Read number

How do I interpret this result?

Best results are usually achieved with at least 40,000 reads per barcode. Below this it is often possible to generate high-accuracy consensus sequences, but not guaranteed.



Read length

How do I interpret this result?

Although longer reads are more likely to recover full-length antibody sequences, NAb-seq will always use the longest reads to make consensus sequences. Thus, good results can be achieved even when most reads are <1 kb.



Read quality

How do I interpret this result?

It is recommended that the reads used to run NAb-seq are basedcalled with the super high accuracy model, which has a Q score cutoff of 10 (~90% accuracy). If you have a lot of reads below this cutoff, the consensus sequences may still contain some errors (usually indels in homopolymer regions).
